definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To clip or cut off a section of an animal 's tail ; to practise a caudectomy .
( transitive ) To reduce (wages); to deduct from (someone).
examples: Her wages were docked by ten dollars.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , informal ) To reduce the wages of (a person).
examples: They docked me ten dollars for breaking the vase.

definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To cut off , bar, or destroy.
( transitive , cooking ) To pierce holes, as pricking dough with a fork , to prevent excessive rising in the oven .
